West Broadway, east side, south from a point slightly north of White Street and showing at the N.E. corner a small 2½ story frame house with a metal sheath. Appearing overhead are the tracks of the Sixth Ave. Elevated line.

May 2, 1938.

P. L. Sperr.

The same location after demolition of the Sixth Avenue "El".

West Broadway, east side, north from White Street, showing prominently the 2½ story frame building at the N. E. corner. These 3 views are more or less similar; one being more inclusive in a vertical plane, to show the dominant N. Y. Telephone Building. This towering edifice is at the convergence of sixth Avenue South and Church Street.

J. Clarence Davies Collection
Museum of N. Y.
